It was a pretty chilly day so not a lot of people were sitting in the plaza for enjoyment besides homeless people. One of the interviewees thought the charging platform was the coolest idea she's seen in all the major cities she's been to and she's not a SF resident (visiting from Dallas but born and raised in NYC) Other than that, the majority of the crowd were people just getting off work, taking a break to have a smoke or waiting to be picked up from a taxi, uber, lyft, etc.
